UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X01000903
KW  - Mutual funds
KW  - Contracting
KW  - Derivatives
AB  - We investigate the option to invest in derivative securities using a large sample of mutual funds. We find that those funds with the greatest transaction-cost benefit tend to permit investment in derivatives, and that funds tend to permit investment only in those derivatives that offer transaction-cost benefits. Our results indicate that a fund's decision to permit investment in derivatives is driven by increased efficiency rather than advisor opportunism.
